---
import BaseLayout from '../app/layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

const title='Image Resizer Plugins';
const description='Install Image Resizer plugins for Chrome and Obsidian. Resize and compress images from the browser or inside an Obsidian vault.';
const chromeUrl='https://chromewebstore.google.com/detail/image-resizer/plkabmchgagilcldimddofngmlapmmng';
const obsidianUrl='https://github.com/jstoolsspace/img-resizer-obsidian';
---
<BaseLayout {title} {description}>
  <section class="plugins-hero">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Plugins</span>
      <h1>Use Image Resizer where your images already are</h1>
    </div>
    <p class="intro-copy"><strong>Resize and compress without changing your workflow.</strong>The Chrome extension handles browser tasks quickly, while the Obsidian plugin works with image files stored inside a vault.</p>
  </section>

  <section class="plugin-grid" aria-label="Available Image Resizer plugins">
    <article>
      <div class="plugin-icon"><span>CR</span></div>
      <p class="plugin-kicker">Chrome Web Store</p>
      <h2>Image Resizer for Chrome</h2>
      <p>Open the extension, choose one or more images, set the output size or format, and download resized files from the browser. Processing is designed for everyday image cleanup before uploads, forms, posts, and messages.</p>
      <a class="plugin-link" href={chromeUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Chrome extension</a>
    </article>

    <article>
      <div class="plugin-icon obsidian"><span>OB</span></div>
      <p class="plugin-kicker">GitHub repository</p>
      <h2>Local Image Resizer for Obsidian</h2>
      <p>Resize, convert, and compress images from an Obsidian vault. The plugin keeps the original file, creates a resized copy, and can update the current note view to point at the new image.</p>
      <a class="plugin-link" href={obsidianUrl} target="_blank" rel="noopener noreferrer">Open Obsidian plugin repo</a>
    </article>
  </section>

  <section class="section plugin-note">
    <div>
      <span class="eyebrow">Local processing</span>
      <h2 class="section-title">The same careful image workflow, packaged for more places</h2>
    </div>
    <p>Both plugins focus on practical resizing and compression. They are built for quick adjustments, predictable output, and image handling that stays close to the device or vault where the source file lives.</p>
  </section>
</BaseLayout>

<style>
.plugins-hero{display:grid;grid-template-columns:minmax(0,1.05fr) minmax(260px,.62fr);gap:4rem;align-items:end;margin:var(--space-6) 0 var(--space-5)}
.plugin-grid{display:grid;grid-template-columns:repeat(2,minmax(0,1fr));gap:1.15rem;margin-bottom:var(--space-7)}
.plugin-grid article{display:grid;align-content:start;gap:.85rem;min-height:360px;padding:1.5rem;border:1px solid var(--line);border-radius:var(--radius);background:#fff;box-shadow:0 18px 45px rgba(23,32,53,.06)}
.plugin-icon{display:grid;place-items:center;width:58px;height:58px;border-radius:16px;background:var(--blue);color:#fff;font-weight:900}
.plugin-icon.obsidian{background:var(--ink)}
.plugin-kicker{color:var(--blue-dark);font-size:.76rem;font-weight:850;letter-spacing:.1em;text-transform:uppercase}
.plugin-grid h2{font-size:clamp(1.45rem,2.4vw,2rem);line-height:1.08;letter-spacing:-.035em}
.plugin-grid p:not(.plugin-kicker){color:var(--ink-soft)}
.plugin-link{align-self:end;display:inline-flex;justify-content:center;width:max-content;margin-top:1rem;padding:.78rem 1rem;border-radius:999px;background:var(--ink);color:#fff;font-weight:800;text-decoration:none}
.plugin-link:hover{background:var(--blue)}
.plugin-note{display:grid;grid-template-columns:.75fr 1fr;gap:3rem;padding:2rem 0;border-top:1px solid var(--line);border-bottom:1px solid var(--line)}
.plugin-note p{color:var(--ink-soft);font-size:1.04rem}
@media(max-width:760px){.plugins-hero,.plugin-grid,.plugin-note{grid-template-columns:1fr}.plugins-hero{gap:1.4rem;margin:2.6rem 0 3rem}.plugin-grid article{min-height:0}.plugin-link{width:100%}}
</style>
